      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Benchmark.AddDeviceBenchmarkEvent",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Benchmark.AddDeviceBenchmarkEvent.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Adds a new device to the engine at the scheduled tick, simulating a node\njoining the network mid-simulation.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Benchmark.BenchmarkConfig.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Benchmark.BenchmarkConfig.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Benchmark.BenchmarkConfig",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Benchmark.BenchmarkConfig.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Fully serialisable description of a benchmark scenario.</p>\n<p>\nA <xref href=\"Engine.Benchmark.BenchmarkConfig\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> defines everything needed to reproduce a\nheadless simulation run deterministically:\n<ul><li>Simulation engine settings (visibility, TTL, packet travel time).</li><li>The initial network layout as a list of <xref href=\"Engine.Benchmark.DeviceBenchmarkDto\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>.</li><li>A timeline of <xref href=\"Engine.Benchmark.BenchmarkEventEntry\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> items that modify the\n        network at specific ticks (toggle, add, remove device).</li><li>The total number of ticks to simulate.</li><li>The list of router names to test; <xref href=\"Engine.Benchmark.BenchmarkRunner\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> will\n        run one full simulation per router and collect results for comparison.</li></ul>\n\n<p>\nInstances are stored as JSON together with their <xref href=\"Engine.Benchmark.BenchmarkSession\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\nresults so a test can be replayed or shared.\n</p>\n"
    },
