      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Core.PacketLimitExceededException",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Core.PacketLimitExceededException.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Thrown by <xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine.RegisterPacket(Engine.Packets.Packet)\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> when the number of\nin-flight packets in the priority queue reaches or exceeds\n<xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine.MaxActivePackets\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>.</p>\n<p>\nThis exception signals that the simulation has entered an unstable state\n(packet storm / routing loop) where more packets are being generated than\nthe network can drain. The host should catch this exception, stop the tick\nloop, and surface the error to the user.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Core.PacketRegisteredEventArgs.yml",
