      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Devices.Device",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Devices.Device.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Abstract base class for all devices in the simulation network.\nA device has a unique identity and a position in 2D space.\nWhen it receives a packet it either forwards it (if it is not the\nintended recipient) or accepts and processes it.</p>\n<p>\nForwarding is delegated to <xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine.RoutePacket(Engine.Packets.Packet%2cEngine.Devices.Device)\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> so that\nthe active <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> is always consulted.\nDevices never reference a concrete router directly.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Devices.EmitterDevice.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Devices.EmitterDevice.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Devices.EmitterDevice",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Devices.EmitterDevice.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">A device that receives command packets from the hub and applies a boolean\nstate to itself (e.g. turning an actuator on or off).</p>\n<p>\nWhen <xref href=\"Engine.Devices.EmitterDevice.ControlFrequencyTicks\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> is greater than zero the hub\nautomatically sends a <xref href=\"Engine.Packets.ControlPacket\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> to this device every\n<xref href=\"Engine.Devices.EmitterDevice.ControlFrequencyTicks\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> ticks, toggling its state from on to\noff and back. Set <xref href=\"Engine.Devices.EmitterDevice.ControlFrequencyTicks\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> to <code>0</code> to\ndisable automatic control signals.\n</p>\n<p>\n<b>Flooding note</b>: with <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.FloodingPacketRouter\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> a\nunicast <xref href=\"Engine.Packets.ControlPacket\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> is re-broadcast at every intermediate hop,\ncreating an exponential number of clones (approximately neighbours^TTL in the\nworst case). The TTL is therefore capped at <xref href=\"Engine.Devices.EmitterDevice.CONTROL_PACKET_TTL\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\nrather than the default packet TTL. When a unicast router is active this has\nno extra cost because the packet follows a single path.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Devices.GeneratorDevice.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Devices.GeneratorDevice.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Devices.GeneratorDevice",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Devices.GeneratorDevice.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">A device that periodically generates sensor-like data packets and routes\nthem toward the hub.</p>\n<p>\nRouting is delegated to <xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine.RoutePacket(Engine.Packets.Packet%2cEngine.Devices.Device)\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> so the\nactive <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> strategy is always used.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Devices.HubDevice.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Devices.HubDevice.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Devices.HubDevice",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Devices.HubDevice.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Represents the central hub (gateway) device of the simulation network.\nThe hub is the designated destination for packets generated by\n<xref href=\"Engine.Devices.GeneratorDevice\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> instances and the root of the network topology.\nIt is registered as the singleton hub inside <xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\nwhen added to the simulation.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Devices.yml",
