      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Packets",
      "Summary": null
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.FloodingPacketRouter.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.FloodingPacketRouter.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers.FloodingPacketRouter",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Routers.FloodingPacketRouter.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Implements a flooding broadcast routing strategy.</p>\n<p>\nWhen asked to route a packet the router queries the supplied\n<xref href=\"Engine.Routers.INetworkTopology\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> for all devices <em>visible</em> to the\nsender and enqueues a cloned copy addressed to each of them.\nFlooding uses <em>visibility</em>  -  not established connections  -  because\nit is inherently a broadcast mechanism that needs no prior topology\nknowledge.\n</p>\n<p>\nThis class is no longer a singleton. The active router instance is stored\non <xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine.Router\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> and is injected into every routing\ncall automatically by <xref href=\"Engine.Devices.Device.Recieve(Engine.Packets.Packet)\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>.\nTo change the routing strategy at runtime replace\n<xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine.Router\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> with a different\n<xref href=\"Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> implementation.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.FullMeshNetworkBuilder.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.FullMeshNetworkBuilder.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers.FullMeshNetworkBuilder",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Routers.FullMeshNetworkBuilder.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">A network-formation strategy that connects every pair of mutually visible\ndevices, producing a full-visibility mesh.</p>\n<p>\nThis mirrors the original implicit behaviour of the engine where visibility\nand connectivity were equivalent: if two devices can see each other they\nare considered connected.\n</p>\n<p>\nNote: as the number of devices grows, the number of edges grows as O(n?).\nFor large networks consider a limited-degree or spanning-tree builder instead.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.IMutableNetworkTopology.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.IMutableNetworkTopology.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers.IMutableNetworkTopology",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Routers.IMutableNetworkTopology.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Extends <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.INetworkTopology\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> with mutation methods so that an\n<xref href=\"Engine.Routers.INetworkBuilder\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> can update the connection graph without\nexposing mutation to routers or other consumers.</p>\n<p>\nOnly <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.INetworkBuilder\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> implementations and\n<xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> should hold a reference to\n<xref href=\"Engine.Routers.IMutableNetworkTopology\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>. All other code (routers, statistics,\nUI) works through the read-only <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.INetworkTopology\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> projection.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.INetworkBuilder.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.INetworkBuilder.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers.INetworkBuilder",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Routers.INetworkBuilder.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Defines the contract for a network-formation (mesh-building) strategy.</p>\n<p>\nA network builder is responsible for deciding which devices establish\nexplicit connections with each other, forming the logical mesh topology.\nIt operates on top of raw visibility data and produces an\n<xref href=\"Engine.Routers.INetworkTopology\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> that the active <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\nthen uses for forwarding decisions.\n</p>\n<p>\nExamples of algorithms that implement this interface:\n<ul><li>Full-mesh  -  every visible pair is connected (current implicit behaviour).</li><li>Limited-degree mesh  -  each device connects to at most <code>K</code> neighbours.</li><li>Minimum spanning tree  -  minimises total edge weight.</li><li>Cluster-head / LEACH-style hierarchy.</li></ul>\n\n<p>\nLike <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>, the active builder is stored on\n<xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> and can be swapped at runtime from the\nUI to compare how different formation strategies affect routing statistics.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.INetworkTopology.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.INetworkTopology.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers.INetworkTopology",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Routers.INetworkTopology.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Represents the logical topology of the network at a given point in time.</p>\n<p>\nThe topology separates two concepts that are intentionally kept distinct:\n<ul><li><span class=\"term\">Visibility</span>\n      Whether two devices are within radio range of each other.\n      Used for broadcast/discovery and as a precondition for establishing a\n      connection. Determined purely by Euclidean distance and\n      <xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine.VisibilityDistance\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>.\n    </li><li><span class=\"term\">Connection</span>\n      An explicit, mutually agreed logical link between two devices.\n      A connection can only exist between mutually visible devices, but not\n      every visible device is necessarily connected (subject to per-device\n      connection limits, protocol decisions, etc.).\n      Unicast routing and network-topology algorithms operate on connections,\n      not on raw visibility.\n    </li></ul>\n\n<p>\nImplementations are owned and updated by the active\n<xref href=\"Engine.Routers.INetworkBuilder\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> and are passed to <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\non every routing call so that routers never need to touch\n<xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> directly.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Routers.IPacketRouter.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Defines the contract for a packet routing strategy.</p>\n<p>\nA router receives a packet from a forwarding device and is responsible for\ndeciding which device(s) the packet should be sent to next.\nImplementations may use different strategies: flooding broadcast,\nshortest-path unicast, gradient routing, etc.\n</p>\n<p>\nThe active router is set on <xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> and is\nconsulted by every device whenever it needs to forward a packet.\nSwapping the router at runtime (e.g. from UI) immediately changes routing\nbehaviour for all subsequent packets, which enables side-by-side protocol\ncomparison on the same network.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.NetworkTopology.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.NetworkTopology.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers.NetworkTopology",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Routers.NetworkTopology.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Default in-memory implementation of <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.IMutableNetworkTopology\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>.</p>\n<p>\nVisibility is computed on-the-fly from device positions and\n<xref href=\"Engine.Core.SimulationEngine.VisibilityDistance\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>; it is never cached\nso it always reflects the current layout.\n</p>\n<p>\nConnections are stored as an adjacency set (both directions) and are\nmanaged exclusively by the active <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.INetworkBuilder\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.SmartFloodingPacketRouter.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.SmartFloodingPacketRouter.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers.SmartFloodingPacketRouter",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Engine.Routers.SmartFloodingPacketRouter.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">An improved flooding router that reduces redundant packet copies by applying\nthree optimisations over the naive <xref href=\"Engine.Routers.FloodingPacketRouter\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>:</p>\n<ol><li><span class=\"term\">Direct delivery</span>\n      If the intended destination (<xref href=\"Engine.Packets.Packet.To\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>) is directly\n      visible from <code class=\"paramref\">sender</code>, the packet is sent\n      <em>only</em> to that device  -  no unnecessary flood copies are made.\n    </li><li><span class=\"term\">No reverse path</span>\n      The packet is never forwarded back to <xref href=\"Engine.Packets.Packet.PreviousHop\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\n      (the device that just sent it here). This eliminates the most common\n      source of duplicate copies in bidirectional flooding.\n    </li><li><span class=\"term\">No source echo</span>\n      The packet is never forwarded back to <xref href=\"Engine.Packets.Packet.From\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\n      (the original source device), preventing useless round-trips.\n    </li></ol>\n<p>\nTogether these rules drastically shrink the clone fan-out compared to the\nnaive flood, especially for unicast packets such as\n<xref href=\"Engine.Packets.ControlPacket\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>, while still guaranteeing delivery\nin any connected topology with sufficient TTL.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Engine.Routers.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Engine.Routers",
      "Summary": null
    },
    {
